article.headline: Fordham 62, La Salle 54
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Marcus Stout scored 20 points and Kevin Anderson added a career-high 15 to lead Fordham to a 62-54 victory over La Salle on Saturday. Brenton Butler added 10 points and Bryant Dunston had seven blocked shots for the Rams (12-7, 5-2 Atlantic 10), who won their fourth straight. Rodney Green scored 12 points for La Salle (9-12, 2-5), which shot 20-for-60, including 1-for-9 from 3-point range. The Explorers trailed for most of the first half, but moved ahead 37-34 with 12:48 left in the game. Anderson then scored 11 points during a 17-4 run to give Fordham a 51-41 lead. La Salle then went on an 11-2 run, closing to 53-52 with 2:29 left, but Stout hit a 3-pointer with 2:05 left and the Rams ended the game with a 9-2 run. Darnell Harris, La Salle's leading scorer, played just 24 minutes, including 11 in the second half, after injuring his right ankle. He finished with three points, well below his 15.8 point average.
